27.title: Searching for a Manta Ray
27.plot: A boy named Ray who lives in Palau, South Pacific, wants to see a Manta Ray in the wild. Jett and the Wild Team do their best to help him find one but end up trapped in a Blue Hole.

1.title: The Right Kite
1.plot: Jett brings a kite to a boy named Akas in the Himalayas, who wants to fly it in a kite festival. Red Pandas take off with the kite and Jett pursues them. When he runs into trouble and gets pinned under a rock, Dizzy shows up with her rescue gear to save the day.

2.title: Shadow Play
2.plot: Mei from Beijing, China requests a shadow puppet to use in a shadow play. Her father is so busy at his dumpling restaurant that he might not make it to her performance. Donnie's Super-Speedy Dumpling Machine comes in handy!

4.title: Aloha Adventure
4.plot: Jett travels to Hawaii to bring Keilani a hula skirt that lights up. On the way to the "Best Hula Dancer" contest it looks like an overflowing volcano will block the road. Donnie uses his jackhammer to get the lava flowing safely into the ocean.

5.title: Puppies for a Princess
5.plot: Princess Maribelle from England asks for sparkly collars for her puppies to wear at her royal tea party. When the puppies escape and run every which way through the garden, Jett and Jerome join forces to round them up.

8.title: Bubble Trouble
8.plot: Callum from Scotland wants bagpipes that blow bubbles so he can play them for Nessie, the Loch Ness Monster. When they float away and drop into the lake, Mira arrives and dives right in. She emerges on the head of Nessie!

9.title: Samba Spectacular
9.plot: Jett has a feathered headdress for Camila from Brazil. She's dancing the samba in a Carnival parade. Jerome comes to help her with her dance moves and Jett uses his Jett Speed to fix Camila's float when it suffers a breakdown.

10.title: Paint Pals
10.plot: Jett takes brushes to Willem in The Netherlands who is going to paint a mural on a sea wall. When the mural is almost done, a storm approaches. Jett and Donnie borrow the propeller from a windmill to dry the painting before it is ruined.

11.title: Race Against Time
11.plot: Jett takes a pair of running shoes that light up to Lorna in Kenya. She's going to run in a big race. While training she crosses paths with a lost baby wildebeest. Bello comes to play a game and reunite the baby with its parents.

13.title: Cold Feet
13.plot: Drew in Canada asks for ice skates so that he can play on an ice hockey team. When he gets to the rink he's so nervous that he can't play. Former Mountie Grand Albert gives Drew confidence-boosting tips so he can score the big goal.

16.title: Paper Rangers
16.plot: Jett brings colorful paper to Yuki in Japan. He and his friends make costumes to play "Paper Rangers" but one friend, Namiko, is moving away. Donnie makes a giant paper robot to give to Namiko as a going-away present.

18.title: Viking voyage
18.plot: Karl from Norway asks for a Viking helmet. He goes to Viking Camp where Jett is mistaken for a dragon. The campers chase Jett onto a ship that heads for a waterfall. Mira comes and pushes them away from disaster.

19.title: A Winning Recipe
19.plot: Martine in Paris, France needs a cake-decorating machine. Her father the baker asks her to ice a giant cake for a party at the Eiffel Tower. When the cake is ready the traffic is terrible. Dizzy flies the cake through the sky over the city.

20.title: Follow That Ghost
20.plot: Brigita from Romania hosts a spooky party and wants a flashlight that projects scary shapes. She hears an eerie sound and follows it. It's her cat stuck in the rafters. Dizzy comes to untangle Jett from spider webs and rescues the kitty.

21.title: Pop Star
21.plot: Vietnamese sisters Sen and Kim are fans of pop star Kellie. They ask for wigs like the one their idol wears. When Kellie's van gets stuck in a rice paddy, Dizzy comes to lead the way to the concert and the sisters are Kellie's special guests.

25.title: Boonying's Bath Time
25.plot: Jerome thinks Jett's job is easy so he takes his place. He delivers a bathtub to Nayan in Thailand. Boonying the elephant takes a bath but is startled by a spray of water and runs off. Jett arrives to help bring Boonying back.

26.title: Family Time
26.plot: Jett brings a magnetic schedule board to Hye Mi in Korea. She has lots of activities every day, from ballet to Taekwondo to music lessons. In a last-minute rush, Dizzy picks up the busy family members and flies them to dinner together.

29.title: Cheese Chase
29.plot: Jett brings cowbells to Sven in Switzerland. Jett learns all about making cheese. But on the way to market the giant wheels of cheese fall off the cart and roll away. Dizzy comes with rescue gear to gather them up.

30.title: Runaway Rex
30.plot: Jett brings a battery to Noah in Denmark, who's built a dinosaur out of plastic blocks. When they power it up the dinosaur escapes and runs through the town. Donnie comes and builds another robot to confront the dinosaur and remove his battery.

31.title: Zebra Scouts
31.plot: Jett brings a divided wooden box to Tendai in Zimbabwe. She's going on a scavenger hunt with her Zebra Scout troop. The box falls into a river and floats away so Grand Albert uses his scout knowledge to build a raft. They retrieve the box and Tendai finds the last item on the list!

33.title: Penguin Parade
33.plot: Jett delivers binoculars to Ella, a girl on the Galapagos Islands. She wants to take her Mom's boat to return a lost penguin to its home in Antarctica. With Donnie's help they overcome obstacles like ice floes, waves and waterspouts and reunite the penguin with its family and friends.

35.title: Blast Off!
35.plot: Jett delivers a spacesuit to a boy named Yun in China, who is going with his class to watch a spaceship take off. Yun gets launched into space by mistake. Donnie comes and builds a rocket and he and Jett go into orbit to find Yun and bring him back to earth.

36.title: Fireman Dad
36.plot: Jett brings a fireman's hat to Stefan in Germany. His dad is a fireman and is coming to school to tell everyone about his job. But a fire breaks out and the fire truck runs out of water. Donnie uses a fountain as a giant shower head, attaching it to a hose and tapping into underground springs to bring enough water to save the day.

38.title: Flying Colors!
38.plot: Meena is going to perform a Bollywood dance with her friends. Jett brings the costumes, but there is a mistake and they are all white instead of many colors. The kids dye the outfits but while they are drying the wind blows them away. Jerome arrives to help Jett gather up the costumes and get them back in time for the performance.

39.title: Pirate Booty
39.plot: Jett takes a pirate hat and eye patch to Cassi, a girl in the British Virgin Islands. She has a map and wants to hunt for treasure. They find an abandoned pirate ship but when they try to sail it starts to sink. Grand Albert comes and uses balloons to fly it through the air and onto dry land.

43.title: Miner Problem
43.plot: Jett goes to Bolivia and brings a miner's helmet to Angelo. His dog has run away. They go with his grandpa to the mine where they take a wild ride on a mining cart, which breaks while underground. Donnie arrives and drills his way through the stone surface to save them.

44.title: Snow Ballin'
44.plot: Jett brings mittens to Stig in Finland, who wants to build the biggest snowman in the country. He and Jett make an enormous snowball that rolls out of control. Then they make another snowball to stop the first one. Donnie comes and builds ramps which bring the snowball together to form a giant snowman.

45.title: Wheel Good Time
45.plot: Jett delivers a stick horse to Carlos in Spain. Carlos wants to play knight and save a princess. Jett becomes his loyal servant. They find his friend Isabel, looking out from a tower, so Carlos says he will rescue her with his flying horse. Dizzy comes and lifts him up to Isabel so that he can finally fulfill his knightly duties.

46.title: Santorini Choo-Choo
46.plot: Katina from Santorini, Greece asks for a braided rope. She wants to play train with her friends and go to the top of the island to watch the sunset. She and her friend argue about who gets to be the conductor and the rope breaks. Jimbo sends Donnie and baggage cart Roy. Donnie builds tracks and Roy gets to be a train and takes everyone to the top of the mountain.

51.title: Wish Upon a Jett
51.plot: Jett arrive with a "magic lamp" for Asya in Turkey. She wants a genie to grant her wishes but the lamp does not work, so Jett offers to become her genie. Dizzy comes and helps to fly a magic carpet to Cappadocia where Asya brings ice cream to her Dad who is riding in a hot air balloon.

46.title: Fish Friends
46.plot: Jett brings a toy castle to Ayesha in The Maldives. She hopes it will cheer up her pet fish, Sir Salty. But he is still sad, so she and Jett take a submarine to a coral reef to find some fish friends. They run into a giant octopus and Mira must come and help them escape its grasp.

-1.title: The Amazing Moritz
-1.plot: Jett brings a magician's hat to Moritz in Austria, who is performing an act with his pet rabbit. As a finale, he will make a piano disappear. The naughty rabbit causes the piano to roll out of the theater. Dizzy comes and uses Rescue Ropes to keep the piano from falling into the Danube River and returns it to the theater for the final trick.

imdb.plot outline: "Super Wings" series revolves around an adorable jet plane named Jett who travels the world delivering packages to children. With every delivery, Jett encounters a new problem that he and his friends the Super Wings must work together to solve. Jett and the Super Wings have the unique ability to transform from planes into amazing heroes who can run, climb, lift, dig and even dive deep under the sea.

plot: A jet plane named Jett travels the world delivering packages to children and solving problems with his friends the Super Wings.

"Super Wings" series revolves around an adorable jet plane named Jett who travels the world delivering packages to children. With every delivery, Jett encounters a new problem that he and his friends the Super Wings must work together to solve. Jett and the Super Wings have the unique ability to transform from planes into amazing heroes who can run, climb, lift, dig and even dive deep under the sea.
